{Speech 24}{}{No problem at all. Only I don't forget such things.}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit}{}{Oh boo-hoo, as if... Let's move on.}
{Speech 25}{}{After that incident I no longer wish to talk to you.@@You bastard! You left@sex@||| me to die in the Wasteland!@@Go to hell...}
{Speech 25 Answer Exit}{}{Hey! I can explain everything!}
{Speech 26}{}{Listen, @sex@|buddy|girl|. You've set yourself up nicely here, and I'm happy with my place too. But I've got one idea, and I keep thinking about it.}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{What are you talking about, Black?}
{Speech 27}{}{Well look. I have a decent clinic here, everything equipped top-class. Patch up, stitch, cut out - anything you like, for your money. So why not go further?}
{Speech 27 Answer 28}{}{Further? I don't understand...}
{Speech 28}{}{It'll all become clear now. We need a replicator, right here in this hole. I know it's quite possible to make a deal with the Hubologists on this. Installing a personal replicator isn't cheap. But on the other hand, it's the next level of comfort in our town! Very convenient. Think about it...}
{Speech 28 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, an interesting idea, thanks, Jack.}
{Speech 28 Answer 29}{}{And who do you need to approach about this, do you know, Black?}
{Speech 29}{}{[Shrugs] I think one of the higher-ups. Where do those robe-wearers have their headquarters? Frisco? Find some bigwig, ask them to explain the terms. I don't think there should be any problems with that.}
{Speech 29 Answer Exit}{}{Yes, thank you, Jack. Maybe that's what we'll do.}
{Speech 30}{}{A personal replicator! The Hubologist technicians brought the structural elements down the stairs and assembled it on site. Then they hooked it up to the town's grid and tuned the replicating programs and the transmitter. To latch onto it, use the terminal. I don't know how, but it works! It's amazing! }
{Speech 30 Answer Exit}{}{I share your optimism, Jack.}
